    "created_at": "2024-08-14T09:36:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-08-14T09:36:08Z",
    "body": "In powershell, deactivating a Venv means just resetting the state of environment variables (most importantly, `$PATH`) to their _previously set_, not _default_ values. If virtualenv is set to be captured by parent shell, deactivating in daughter shell may not actually do anything. How are you starting starship inside the terminal? Do you by any chance call a custom `pwsh.exe` command?",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
