    "created_at": "2024-08-20T07:54:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-08-20T07:54:41Z",
    "body": "I can replicate the issue in VSCode after disabling the starship altogether, with no custom commands:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7cea787d-f5ab-4810-9c75-67c3cd4f07e1)\r\n\r\nLike I said, it has nothing to do with starship, and only has to do with how editor (VSCode or PyCharm) sets environment variables before invoking the pwsh.exe. Activating/deactivating environments is technically implemented by setting and resetting environment variables, and starship's python module only ever reads them.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
